00:54.316 --> 00:57.109
I have little use for their kind in years.

00:59.445 --> 01:01.112
In face of difficulty,

01:01.113 --> 01:05.114
large grievances become...

01:05.117 --> 01:07.701
so minor.

02:19.108 --> 02:21.067
Oh, wait!

02:21.067 --> 02:23.194
I wanna try something.

02:35.581 --> 02:38.543
Doctors say the longer

02:38.585 --> 02:42.381
you stay in a coma, the less
likely you are to wake up.

02:42.382 --> 02:46.466
Pfff! Doctors.

02:46.467 --> 02:48.721
You really have a way with words.

02:55.144 --> 02:58.811
Can you tell me a story
about being a gypsy?

02:58.812 --> 03:01.733
You guys realize I'm half Italian, right?

03:01.733 --> 03:04.902
We do. It's just no one cares.

03:07.656 --> 03:09.907
All right.

03:12.036 --> 03:13.995
One time Nicolai caught a fairy.

03:14.037 --> 03:16.662
What do you mean a fairy?

03:16.663 --> 03:18.831
I mean a fairy. What am I supposed to mean?

03:18.834 --> 03:22.420
OK, go on.

03:22.462 --> 03:25.466
I was at his house one night.

03:25.466 --> 03:27.466
It was the summer,

03:27.467 --> 03:30.596
so it was just scorching hot.

03:30.597 --> 03:33.847
Must have been eight or nine.

03:33.847 --> 03:35.848
And he says, "You wanna see something?"

03:35.849 --> 03:38.477
So he turns off all the lights,

03:38.478 --> 03:40.438
and he gave me this jar

03:40.480 --> 03:42.483
with a little light inside,

03:44.484 --> 03:46.901
And I go, "Nic, that's just...

03:46.902 --> 03:49.197
that's a lightning bug", and he goes,

03:49.198 --> 03:51.948
"No, Peter...

03:51.949 --> 03:54.075
look closer".

03:54.078 --> 03:56.829
Yeah?

03:56.829 --> 03:59.789
And I held it up...

03:59.792 --> 04:01.751
and I shit you not,

04:01.751 --> 04:05.337
there's this little person inside the jar,

04:05.340 --> 04:07.799
a little girl,

04:07.799 --> 04:10.216
no bigger than a thumbnail.

04:10.217 --> 04:12.218
And her wings are so beautiful

04:12.221 --> 04:14.222
like a dragonfly.

04:16.309 --> 04:19.976
And this little light...

04:19.978 --> 04:23.357
What was she wearing?

04:23.357 --> 04:25.690
- What?
- So I go to Nic like,

04:25.692 --> 04:28.612
"Holy! Where did you find her?"

04:28.612 --> 04:30.821
And all he says is,

04:30.822 --> 04:32.990
"She was just...

04:32.990 --> 04:37.452
flying around the
porch light with the moths".

04:37.454 --> 04:39.999
She must have gotten lost.

04:40.040 --> 04:42.333
Yeah. You know, at first he tried

04:42.334 --> 04:45.252
to catch 'em with his hands,
but I guess she stung him.

04:45.252 --> 04:47.505
- Fairies sting?
- Oh! You have no idea.

04:47.505 --> 04:49.714
Fairies are meaner than fucking hornets!

04:49.716 --> 04:50.757
- Who knew?
- Yeah.

04:50.800 --> 04:53.802
So what did you do with her?

04:53.803 --> 04:56.430
We just kept her for a while.

04:56.430 --> 04:59.684
What did she eat?

04:59.685 --> 05:01.644
- Flies.
- Ugh!

05:01.644 --> 05:04.398
Ha! Ha! Ha! Gross!

05:04.398 --> 05:06.483
Pretty fairies do not eat flies.

05:06.524 --> 05:09.526
Just grabbed them out of the air

05:09.528 --> 05:11.529
and tore 'em apart.

05:11.529 --> 05:13.531
Mm! Stop it.

05:13.531 --> 05:15.783
Better than watching
tarantulas go after crickets.

05:26.211 --> 05:28.172
So what happened to her?

05:30.882 --> 05:33.384
She died.

05:33.386 --> 05:36.346
One day it was just a tiny old
lady in the bottom of the jar.

05:39.434 --> 05:43.269
At first, I thought she
was just napping so I shook it.

05:45.398 --> 05:48.149
Definitely dead.

05:51.446 --> 05:55.156
No one can fucking live like that.

07:53.274 --> 07:55.694
Clear your head.

07:58.238 --> 08:00.238
Must do what he said.

08:00.240 --> 08:02.744
Clear your head. Clear
your head. Clear your head.

08:12.252 --> 08:15.504
Fucking psychic spooky weird twin shit!

08:15.505 --> 08:17.507
Fuck!

08:19.843 --> 08:21.887
...damn hands up, bitch!

08:24.430 --> 08:27.267
I can't have my baby here.

08:29.810 --> 08:32.479
We always have had time for each other.

08:32.480 --> 08:36.568
God does not want us to be
happy. He wants us to be strong.

08:44.283 --> 08:47.328
Welcome to the Order of
the Dragon, Dr. Chasseur.

09:11.479 --> 09:15.730
...Quam Misericors est Deus,

09:15.732 --> 09:19.068
Pius et Justus.

09:19.110 --> 09:20.738
O...

09:22.739 --> 09:24.950
Your hands.

09:31.791 --> 09:35.125
O Quam Misericors est Deus,

09:35.126 --> 09:38.879
Pius et Justus.

09:45.846 --> 09:48.264
When the moon is full, do
you walk in the skin of a wolf?

09:48.306 --> 09:52.936
We and the barons and
magnates of our kingdom

09:52.979 --> 09:55.772
shall bear and have...

09:55.773 --> 09:57.816
and do choose and agree

09:57.859 --> 10:00.359
to bear and wear the sign

10:00.360 --> 10:02.613
or effigy of the dragon

10:02.653 --> 10:05.614
incurved into this form of a circle...

10:05.615 --> 10:09.158
its tail winding around its neck...

10:09.160 --> 10:12.496
divided through the middle of its back

10:12.498 --> 10:16.249
with blood forming a red cross.

10:16.250 --> 10:19.879
But it remains untouched by that blood,

10:19.879 --> 10:21.965
just as all of those

10:22.008 --> 10:25.258
who fight under the banner of
the glorious martyr St. George

10:25.259 --> 10:27.345
remain untouched by the beast.

10:27.345 --> 10:30.765
The beast is the devil

10:30.807 --> 10:34.225
appearing on Earth as
a radiant heavenly being,

10:34.227 --> 10:36.938
claiming to be God.

10:38.941 --> 10:42.485
But you shall root him out.

10:46.032 --> 10:48.282
Let Him serve as your guide

10:48.325 --> 10:50.785
and from this day forward...

10:52.830 --> 10:55.455
...let it be

10:55.456 --> 10:57.835
the only one you bear.

11:01.212 --> 11:03.172
May you strike down

11:03.215 --> 11:06.509
God's enemies and smite them

11:06.551 --> 11:09.804
from the Earth in his name.

11:16.979 --> 11:20.648
It's gotta be him.

11:20.648 --> 11:22.734
So why don't I believe it?

11:29.575 --> 11:31.157
Who are you?

11:31.158 --> 11:32.994
What are you?

11:50.052 --> 11:53.347
You're going to lose your soul.

11:53.389 --> 11:55.850
Ahhh!

12:02.355 --> 12:04.357
Cool view!

12:04.359 --> 12:08.278
OK, who did you blow to get this room?

12:08.278 --> 12:11.282
- Are you OK?
- Yeah.

12:11.282 --> 12:13.243
Yeah, I'm fine.

12:13.283 --> 12:15.244
I just woke up.

12:15.244 --> 12:18.039
OK, um, we brought
some DVDs for you to watch.

12:20.960 --> 12:23.628
Or we could do whatever you want.

12:23.671 --> 12:25.672
Yeah.

12:25.672 --> 12:28.423
Don't you like Scrabble
or something? I mean,

12:28.424 --> 12:31.595
I can download the app
on my phone if you want.

12:38.350 --> 12:40.311
Do, do you see something?

12:40.354 --> 12:42.815
No, I don't see anything.

12:44.816 --> 12:47.777
Um... whatever you guys
want to do, I'll do.

12:51.196 --> 12:53.868
Lys.

12:56.703 --> 13:00.330
I'm sorry.

13:00.331 --> 13:02.375
I'm sorry.

13:04.794 --> 13:06.797
You're my best friend.

13:08.798 --> 13:11.801
I'll be OK.

13:11.844 --> 13:14.345
I'll be OK.

13:22.269 --> 13:24.272
Jesus.

13:28.902 --> 13:32.321
Hey. How's she doing?

13:32.321 --> 13:35.658
I hate it here, Dad.
Chrissy hates it here too.

13:37.660 --> 13:39.870
She said she was feeling better and...

13:39.871 --> 13:42.248
really, really wants to stay with us.

13:42.289 --> 13:44.542
Did she actually say that?

13:44.585 --> 13:48.294
Uh... she, she didn't have to.

13:48.296 --> 13:50.547
Yeah, friends always know
what other friends are thinking.

13:50.548 --> 13:53.094
- Always.
- Yeah.

13:57.597 --> 14:00.725
Our girl's been through
a lot lately, and I know

14:00.768 --> 14:03.436
that hospitals are no fun,
but Dr. Godfrey thinks she needs

14:03.477 --> 14:06.648
to stay here a little bit longer, and
I need to trust his judgment on this.

14:06.690 --> 14:08.609
- Dad...
- Hey.

14:10.443 --> 14:13.947
She knows that you two
love her so very much,

14:13.989 --> 14:16.825
like a sister,

14:16.866 --> 14:19.994
and that's what she needs right now.

14:19.994 --> 14:21.455
OK?

14:21.495 --> 14:23.289
Yeah.

14:23.330 --> 14:25.167
OK. Come on.

14:52.777 --> 14:54.571
Ahh...

14:56.907 --> 14:58.908
You're still so beautiful...

15:00.910 --> 15:03.496
...as beautiful as the day I first saw you.

15:10.296 --> 15:14.381
You, uh, probably have to get home.

15:16.509 --> 15:18.470
OK.

15:20.471 --> 15:23.431
You don't?

15:23.432 --> 15:25.643
What?

15:25.643 --> 15:27.604
Have to go home?

15:30.273 --> 15:32.275
Of course I do.

15:48.499 --> 15:50.793
Let me help you, darling.

16:24.244 --> 16:25.703
There.

16:25.745 --> 16:29.374
Better.

17:01.197 --> 17:03.200
I think you got it.

17:05.201 --> 17:08.742
Letha is fucking Peter Rumancek.

17:08.743 --> 17:10.746
What?!

17:10.747 --> 17:12.750
She told you this?

17:12.750 --> 17:15.336
Of course not. She doesn't
tell me anything.

17:15.376 --> 17:17.461
Well, then how do you know?

17:17.462 --> 17:20.256
Her phone, text messages.

17:20.259 --> 17:22.759
Marie, you had no right.

17:22.759 --> 17:25.428
I mean, that's an invasion of her privacy.

17:25.429 --> 17:28.098
Our daughter claims she has

17:28.140 --> 17:30.848
been impregnated by an angel.

17:30.849 --> 17:34.060
An angel, Norman! Now, she's sleeping

17:34.061 --> 17:36.064
with a boy that half
the people in Hemlock Grove

17:36.106 --> 17:39.023
- think is a serial killer.
- Uh, well they don't just think

17:39.025 --> 17:41.444
he's a serial killer, Marie,
they think he's a werewolf,

17:41.486 --> 17:43.487
and that is insane.

17:43.490 --> 17:46.451
Do you know that one of my
patients originated that rumor?

17:46.491 --> 17:48.492
It's character assassination

17:48.492 --> 17:51.538
by a traumatized 14-year-old girl.

17:51.578 --> 17:54.000
I need you to be her father,

17:54.000 --> 17:56.000
not her friend.

17:59.798 --> 18:01.381
OK.

18:01.423 --> 18:04.049
I'll talk to her.

18:04.092 --> 18:06.801
Hey, guys, I'm home.

18:32.453 --> 18:34.539
- Hey.
- Hey.

18:37.836 --> 18:40.211
Um...

18:40.212 --> 18:43.884
your mom... your mom
got ahold of your cell phone.

18:43.923 --> 18:47.135
We know about Peter.

18:50.137 --> 18:54.808
- Dad...
- She had no right.

18:54.809 --> 18:56.894
Was it, um...

18:56.895 --> 18:58.855
was it your first time...

18:58.896 --> 19:01.567
in a manner of speaking?

19:01.567 --> 19:04.986
- Yeah.
- It's not a bad thing.

19:05.028 --> 19:07.240
I mean, don't ever let anyone

19:07.240 --> 19:09.201
put in your head that sex is,

19:09.241 --> 19:11.284
is a bad thing.

19:11.326 --> 19:13.494
Is this as awkward for you as it is for me?

19:13.538 --> 19:15.539
- Yeah!
- Ha!

19:17.540 --> 19:20.376
Sit.

19:24.506 --> 19:28.217
But lying, lying to me, to us,

19:28.218 --> 19:30.221
hiding things,

19:30.261 --> 19:33.057
that's a problem.

19:33.057 --> 19:36.434
We're a family. We don't keep secrets

19:36.476 --> 19:39.396
- from each other.
- I'm in love with him.

19:43.482 --> 19:46.734
People see someone like Peter
as a blank piece of paper

19:46.736 --> 19:49.280
they can just put everything
they're afraid of on.

19:51.407 --> 19:53.867
You know how people are.

19:53.867 --> 19:56.119
I mean...

19:56.121 --> 19:58.705
what do you think people say about Shelley?

20:03.044 --> 20:05.048
Do you trust me?

20:09.925 --> 20:11.928
Hi.

20:20.936 --> 20:23.731
I hope this isn't a bad time.

20:27.028 --> 20:28.944
He's upstairs.

20:28.987 --> 20:32.656
Oh. Uh... No, I'm not here to see him.

20:32.698 --> 20:35.326
I mean, I pray for him,

20:35.327 --> 20:37.288
but... I came here

20:37.328 --> 20:39.330
because I thought
maybe you needed a friend.

20:41.333 --> 20:44.376
I figured this hasn't been easy on you.

20:44.419 --> 20:47.128
Wow! That sounds so stupid.

20:47.130 --> 20:50.174
Of course this hasn't been
easy on you. Uh... what I mean

20:50.215 --> 20:53.386
- is that...
- It's not stupid.

20:55.972 --> 20:58.016
Can I give you a hug?

21:04.689 --> 21:07.898
- Hey!
- Hey.

21:07.900 --> 21:11.987
Uh, I just wanted you
to know how sorry I am.

21:11.990 --> 21:14.071
I'm kind of sick about the whole thing.

21:14.073 --> 21:16.741
I was trying to think of
the last time I talked to Roman

21:16.742 --> 21:18.742
before this and...

21:18.743 --> 21:20.744
I think I was a bitch to him.

21:20.746 --> 21:23.375
I'm sure that's not true.

21:23.375 --> 21:26.794
Uh, anyway I made him this.

21:26.836 --> 21:29.423
If you wouldn't mind bringing it to him...

21:29.423 --> 21:31.259
Yeah, of course.

21:31.299 --> 21:34.718
Thanks. I really...

21:34.721 --> 21:37.057
I hope he's OK.

21:43.605 --> 21:46.439
What was that about?

21:46.481 --> 21:49.568
Evidently, Ashley Valentine
does have a soul.

21:52.529 --> 21:54.530
So, I wanted to ask you something.

21:54.573 --> 21:57.659
I want you to come to dinner at my house.

22:01.953 --> 22:04.540
So, you said you
found me through my website?

22:04.583 --> 22:07.000
Yes. Not many people who do...

22:07.001 --> 22:09.126
what you do in the tri-state area.

22:09.127 --> 22:11.798
Fair enough.

22:11.798 --> 22:14.384
No offense, but you don't really
seem like the type to come

22:14.425 --> 22:17.803
- to a person like me.
- Excuse me?

22:17.846 --> 22:20.182
Well, there...

22:20.182 --> 22:22.769
tend to be certain life
events that bring clients

22:22.808 --> 22:24.934
to my doorstep...

22:24.935 --> 22:28.106
a death in the family, mother, father,

22:28.146 --> 22:30.732
sometimes a favorite uncle.

22:30.733 --> 22:34.153
Infidelity is another big one
too, clichÃ© as that may be.

22:34.194 --> 22:37.365
And then there are those tragic
folk who wake up one morning

22:37.406 --> 22:40.367
and remember they've been molested...

22:40.367 --> 22:42.369
sometimes by their favorite uncle.

22:45.205 --> 22:47.208
But you...

22:47.250 --> 22:50.127
your problem doesn't fall into
any of those categories, do you?

22:52.631 --> 22:56.259
Your problem seems to me to be much more...

22:56.259 --> 22:57.926
internal.

22:57.971 --> 23:00.178
How do you figure?

23:00.179 --> 23:03.599
Well, for one, I could smell it on your
breath the second you walked in the door.

23:03.644 --> 23:06.435
Don't worry. There's no judgments here.

23:08.355 --> 23:10.355
You can talk to me...

23:10.356 --> 23:12.317
about anything.

23:12.357 --> 23:15.403
I want to talk to you about family.

23:15.444 --> 23:17.529
I sense you don't have much of one.

23:17.530 --> 23:20.784
Your family, actually. A cousin,

23:20.826 --> 23:23.910
if I'm not mistaken.

23:23.913 --> 23:27.125
I know what you think you're
looking for, but you'd be wrong.

23:27.165 --> 23:29.208
Then why am I here?

23:29.250 --> 23:32.002
To find what you've been looking for.

23:32.044 --> 23:35.464
Like I said, there are no judgments here.

23:35.509 --> 23:37.924
You can talk to me

23:37.924 --> 23:39.926
about anything.

23:44.890 --> 23:47.309
I'm not sure I can trust myself anymore.

23:50.480 --> 23:53.357
I'm afraid I've lost my path to God.

23:53.398 --> 23:55.942
- When you say God, you mean...
- I mean God.

23:55.943 --> 23:59.154
Right. I'm sorry.

23:59.155 --> 24:01.865
I don't get many big Gs in here.

24:01.865 --> 24:04.410
And the ones I do are usually
enjoying my other services.

24:11.083 --> 24:13.086
Interesting, though...

24:15.505 --> 24:17.423
...that as a woman of faith
you have such a problem

24:17.464 --> 24:19.800
with control.

24:26.098 --> 24:28.183
Let me see your hands.

24:28.184 --> 24:30.227
Why?

24:30.230 --> 24:32.646
Because it's important that I see.

24:42.155 --> 24:45.951
Look, you came here for a reason
and I let you in for a reason,

24:45.992 --> 24:48.078
so let's just put all our shit
aside and trust each other

24:48.078 --> 24:49.997
for two seconds.

25:06.598 --> 25:09.726
It's in every part of you.

25:14.021 --> 25:16.692
You're not lying.

25:16.692 --> 25:19.528
You have been searching.

25:19.528 --> 25:21.819
Uh...

25:21.820 --> 25:23.906
Mmm...

25:30.747 --> 25:34.290
Will you tell me what you saw?

25:34.291 --> 25:36.515
What you felt?

25:38.423 --> 25:40.423
Please.

25:40.423 --> 25:42.467
Please, I need to know.

26:05.530 --> 26:07.659
Let me restore you.

26:24.675 --> 26:28.761
Would you like to hear God's voice again?

26:28.762 --> 26:30.763
Yes.

26:30.765 --> 26:32.809
Yes...

26:59.336 --> 27:02.838
Ah, Mrs. Godfrey.

27:02.838 --> 27:04.799
Sorry. Did we, uh, call you?

27:04.840 --> 27:07.384
No. As a matter of fact, you did not,

27:07.385 --> 27:09.386
and you should have by now.

27:09.386 --> 27:11.432
Why isn't my son's car ready yet?

27:11.472 --> 27:14.644
Uh, we had to change the starter

27:14.684 --> 27:16.769
and some electrical...

27:16.810 --> 27:18.896
Parts for a car this old aren't...

27:18.896 --> 27:20.857
easy to find.

27:20.898 --> 27:24.484
I want it in driving
condition, and I want it now.

27:30.826 --> 27:33.285
Marie.

27:33.327 --> 27:35.453
Olivia.

27:37.455 --> 27:40.541
- Car trouble?
- Well, you know, he thinks it's nothing,

27:40.542 --> 27:42.923
but every time I drive it,
I hear this rattling.

27:42.962 --> 27:45.714
Prevention is the best cure.

27:45.759 --> 27:47.925
How is Roman?

27:47.967 --> 27:50.801
No...

27:50.803 --> 27:52.804
change yet.

27:52.807 --> 27:55.223
Letha's been stopping by
quite a bit to see him.

27:55.223 --> 27:58.144
Truly lovely girl.

27:58.184 --> 28:01.564
Thank you. Norman also?

28:01.606 --> 28:03.732
Yes, a...

28:03.732 --> 28:05.984
a great support as always.

28:06.028 --> 28:08.070
Yes, he is.

28:08.111 --> 28:12.032
It's a pleasure running
into you. It's been so long.

28:12.076 --> 28:13.576
It has.

28:16.954 --> 28:18.915
Olivia.

28:18.957 --> 28:22.250
He's in our thoughts.

28:22.251 --> 28:24.963
Good luck with the rattle.

28:45.817 --> 28:48.611
Thanks, Nic.

28:48.653 --> 28:50.865
What's that?

28:58.871 --> 29:02.083
We were worried you might be a vegetarian.

29:02.125 --> 29:05.376
No. The steak's good.

29:05.419 --> 29:07.298
It's great, Mom. Thanks.

29:07.338 --> 29:10.674
She uses a special marinade.

29:10.674 --> 29:12.635
What's in it again?

29:12.676 --> 29:14.971
Just a little bit of love.

29:22.227 --> 29:25.313
Did you guys see that picture
in the paper of the guy

29:25.314 --> 29:28.525
walking down Liberty Avenue
with a leopard on his back?

29:28.528 --> 29:30.319
No.

29:30.361 --> 29:32.696
No.

29:32.740 --> 29:34.740
Sorry.

29:34.781 --> 29:36.992
Oh! Well, there was this guy

29:36.992 --> 29:39.118
walking naked down Liberty Avenue

29:39.119 --> 29:42.375
with a leopard on his back.

29:42.414 --> 29:44.415
